codeSystems.name: JurisdictionValueSet
codeSystems.title: Jurisdiction ValueSet
codeSystems.description:
This value set defines a base set of codes for country, country subdivision and region    for indicating where a resource is intended to be used.   
   
   Note: The codes for countries and country subdivisions are taken from    [ISO 3166](https://www.iso.org/iso-3166-country-codes.html)    while the codes for "supra-national" regions are from    [UN Standard country or area codes for statistical use (M49)](http://unstats.un.org/unsd/methods/m49/m49.htm).

codeSystems.name: GenderIdentityValueSet
codeSystems.title: Gender Identity Value Set
codeSystems.description: This valueset specifies terms which represent an individual's personal experience of being a woman, man, nonbinary, or how the person prefers to self-describe. People may identify with more than one gender identity or use different gender identities in different settings. This resource is an informative value set; a normative subset containing the expanded values can be found on Canada Health Infoway's [Terminology Server](https://infocentral.infoway-inforoute.ca/en/tools/standards-tools/terminology-server).

codeSystems.name: RecordedGenderValueSet
codeSystems.title: Recorded Gender Value Set
codeSystems.description: The scope of this subset is to represent genders as used in healthcare data systems. This includes commonly used gender identities for administrative and clinical purposes. This resource is an informative value set; a normative subset containing the expanded values can be found on Canada Health Infoway's [Terminology Server](https://infocentral.infoway-inforoute.ca/en/tools/standards-tools/terminology-server).

This resource is an informative value set; a normative subset containing the expanded values can be found on Canada Health Infoway's [Terminology Server](https://infocentral.infoway-inforoute.ca/en/tools/standards-tools/terminology-server).
